 As nearly half the acreage afire burns within 150 miles, specialists in the logistics center marshal resources from around the nation.
 In one leg of the L-shaped logistics room, the intelligence division keeps track of fires around the country.
 National Guard troops in camouflage fatigues march toward trucks for transportation to the fire lines.
 Then the craft roar aloft toward the smoky mountains to the north.
 It will take fall rains and winter snow to douse many of the nation's fires.
